wpm.data

Class HTMLTagPrototype

  • java.lang.Object
    • wpm.data.HTMLTagPrototype
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.lang.Cloneable, java.lang.Comparable<HTMLTagPrototype>

    public class HTMLTagPrototype
extends java.lang.Object
implements java.lang.Comparable<HTMLTagPrototype>, java.lang.Cloneable
    This class represents a single element (i.e. tag) in an HTML tree.

    • Constructor Detail

      • HTMLTagPrototype

        public HTMLTagPrototype(java.lang.String initTagName,
                        boolean initHasClosingTag)
        Constructor that initializes the minimal requirements, meaning the name of the tag and whether it has a closing tag. Note that legal parents and attributes must be subsequently provided in order to setup this object properly.
        Parameters:
        initTagName - Tag name for this object, like "p" for a paragraph.
        initHasClosingTag - Used to initialize this object, true is for HTML elements that have closing tags, false is for those that don't, like "br".

      • clone

        public HTMLTagPrototype clone()
        This class employs the prototype design pattern in that whenever we wish to add a new tag to our tree, we start by cloning a similar one. This method provides the clone implementation, initializing the object with the same name but empty attributes.
        Overrides:
        clone in class java.lang.Object
        Returns:
        A newly constructed tag object it the same tag name and attributes, but empty attribute values.
